 - the appellant’s integration in the Canadian community outside his family;  
- the appellant’s modification of his behavior as to his residency obligation after the 
issuance of the deportation order and his work in Canada during that time;  
- the hardship that the appellant would face if his appeal was dismissed and if he was 
separated from his wife and children in Canada;  
- the objective of the Act  of “reunification of families in Canada”

[35]  When the tribunal looks at the negative factors, the tribunal sees  
- a legal impediment that is  important but not overwhelming;   
- the short duration of the appellant’s stay in Canada;  
- the appellant’s  establishment in Iran more important than  his establishment in Canada;  
- the appellant’s absence of imperious reasons to be away from Canada during the period 
of reference and the fact that the he did not return at the first opportunity;  
- the fact that the appellant’s life would not be at risk in Iran if his appeal was dismissed

